sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1675004
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The constitutive promoter J23119, the ribosome binding site B0034 and the functional gene NhaA were used in this new standard part. This part is available for the bacteria to survive in alkaline environment.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: JIAQI XU
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The sequence of J23119 is found through the standard part BBa_J23119. http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_J23119 The sequence of ribosome binding site B0034 is found through the standard part BBa_B0034.http://parts.igem.org/Part:BBa_B0034 The sequence of gene NhaA is found through Genbank http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/NC_000913.3?report=genbank&from=17489&to=18655

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1675000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The gene,NhaA, is the archetypal sodium-proton antiporter in E. coli. It is the only member of the family that is absolutely required by E. coli for survival in high-salt conditions, under alkaline stress, or in the presence of otherwise toxic Li+ concentration. NhaA catalyzes the exchange of 2 H+ per Na+. Therefore, nhaA could make sure E. coli???s survival under alkaline pH, which are in desperate need in our project.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: JIAQI XU
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. Sequence found through Genbank http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nuccore/NC_000913.3?report=genbank&from=17489&to=18655

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
